---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { site } from "../config";

// Date this policy text last changed (not the build date). Edit when you revise
// the wording so the "Last updated" line below stays meaningful.
//
// NOTE: This is a sensible, privacy-friendly starting point — not legal advice.
// Review it (and the name/links) before you publish, and adjust for your
// jurisdiction.
const lastUpdated = "1 January 2026";
---

<Layout
    title="Privacy"
    description="How this site handles your data — no cookies, no advertising, no accounts, and no analytics or tracking. Written to meet EU/UK GDPR, US (CCPA/CalOPPA), and Canadian (PIPEDA/Law 25) expectations."
>
    <article class="page prose">
        <h1 class="page__title">Privacy Policy</h1>

        <p class="lede">
            This is a personal photography and writing site. It is built to
            respect your privacy by default: no cookies, no advertising, no
            cross-site tracking, no accounts, and no forms that collect your
            personal data. This page explains the little data that is involved
            and the rights you have, wherever you live.
        </p>

        <p><em>Last updated: {lastUpdated}.</em></p>

        <h2>Who is responsible</h2>
        <p>
            This site is operated by me, {site.name}{site.nameZh && (
                <> (<span class="name-zh">{site.nameZh}</span>)</>
            )}. For the purposes of data-protection
            law I am the “data controller” (EU/UK GDPR), the individual
            accountable for personal information (Canada’s PIPEDA), and the
            person in charge of personal information (Québec’s Law 25). You can
            reach me through the <a class="text-link" href="/contact"
                >contact page</a
            >.
        </p>

        <h2>The short version</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>No cookies are set by this site.</li>
            <li>No advertising, ad networks, or cross-site tracking.</li>
            <li>No accounts, logins, or newsletters.</li>
            <li>No contact forms — nothing on this site asks you to type in personal data.</li>
            <li>
                No analytics and no visitor tracking of any kind — nothing is
                stored on your device except an optional theme preference.
            </li>
            <li>
                I do not sell, rent, or trade your information, and I never
                share it for marketing.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What is collected, and why</h2>

        <h3>Analytics</h3>
        <p>
            This site uses <strong>no analytics</strong> — no third-party
            analytics service, no first-party visitor counter, and no tracking
            script of any kind. Nothing is loaded or stored to measure your
            visit, and you are not tracked across sites or over time.
        </p>

        <h3>Server logs (hosting provider)</h3>
        <p>
            The site is served by a third-party hosting provider. As with
            essentially every website, the host automatically records standard
            technical request data — including your IP address, the page
            requested, and your browser type — to deliver the site reliably and
            protect it against abuse and attacks. These logs are retained for a
            short period under the provider’s own policies.
        </p>

        <h3>Your theme preference</h3>
        <p>
            If you switch between light and dark mode, that single choice is
            saved in your browser’s local storage so the site remembers it on
            your next visit. It stays on your device, is never sent to me, and
            is not used to identify you. You can clear it at any time through
            your browser settings.
        </p>

        <h3>Links to other sites</h3>
        <p>
            The site links out to profiles such as Instagram, LinkedIn, and
            GitHub. Once you follow one of those links you are on a
            third-party service governed by its own privacy policy, not this
            one.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
        <p>
            This site uses <strong>no cookies</strong>. The only thing stored on
            your device is the optional theme preference described above, which
            is strictly necessary to remember your display choice. Because
            nothing non-essential is stored on or read from your device, no
            cookie-consent banner is required under the EU ePrivacy rules or the
            UK’s PECR. I also honour “Do Not Track” and Global Privacy Control
            browser signals — though in practice there is nothing to opt out of,
            because the site does not track you or build a profile of you.
        </p>

        <h2>Legal bases (EU/UK GDPR)</h2>
        <p>
            Where the GDPR or UK GDPR applies, the limited processing above
            rests on my <strong>legitimate interests</strong> (Article 6(1)(f)):
            keeping the site secure, available, and free of abuse. This processing is
            minimal and non-intrusive, no information identifying you is stored,
            and so no separate consent is required. I do not process any
            special-category (sensitive) data, and there is no automated
            decision-making or profiling.
        </p>

        <h2>Who I share information with</h2>
        <p>
            I do not sell, rent, or trade personal information, and I do not
            share it for advertising. My hosting provider processes limited
            technical data (such as request logs) on my behalf, strictly to
            serve and protect the site. They act as a processor under my
            instructions. I may disclose information only if I am legally
            required to do so.
        </p>

        <h2>International data transfers</h2>
        <p>
            This site is reachable worldwide, and the providers above may
            process data in countries other than your own, including the United
            States. Where required for visitors in the EU, the UK, or Canada,
            those transfers rely on appropriate safeguards — such as the
            providers’ Standard Contractual Clauses and data-processing terms.
        </p>

        <h2>How long data is kept</h2>
        <p>
            I keep no personal data about you myself. My hosting provider’s
            technical logs are retained for the short periods set out in its own
            policy.
        </p>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>
            Your rights depend on where you live. Because this site does not
            store information that identifies you, I often will not be able to
            connect a request to any specific data about you — but you are
            welcome to exercise any of the rights below.
        </p>

        <h3>European Union &amp; United Kingdom</h3>
        <p>
            Under the GDPR and UK GDPR you have the right to access, rectify,
            erase, restrict, or object to the processing of your personal data
            (including objecting to legitimate-interest processing), and the
            right to data portability. You will not be subject to automated
            decision-making. You may also lodge a complaint with your local
            supervisory authority — in the UK, the Information Commissioner’s
            Office (<a
                href="https://ico.org.uk"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a
            >).
        </p>

        <h3>United States (including California)</h3>
        <p>
            Where US state privacy laws such as California’s CCPA/CPRA apply, you
            have the right to know, access, delete, and correct personal
            information, and to opt out of its sale or sharing. I do
            <strong>not</strong> sell or share personal information, have not done
            so, and do not use it for targeted advertising. I will never discriminate
            against you for exercising a privacy right.
        </p>

        <h3>Canada</h3>
        <p>
            Under PIPEDA and Québec’s Law 25 you have the right to access the
            personal information held about you, to request corrections, and to
            withdraw consent. You may complain to the Office of the Privacy
            Commissioner of Canada (<a
                href="https://www.priv.gc.ca"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer">priv.gc.ca</a
            >) or, in Québec, to the Commission d’accès à l’information.
        </p>

        <p>
            To exercise any of these rights, get in touch through the <a
                class="text-link"
                href="/contact">contact page</a
            >. I will respond within the time required by the law that applies to
            you.
        </p>

        <h2>Children’s privacy</h2>
        <p>
            This site is not directed to children and I do not knowingly collect
            personal information from children (under 13 in the United States, or
            the equivalent age — up to 16 — in parts of the EU). If you believe a
            child has provided personal information, please contact me and I will
            address it.
        </p>

        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>
            The site is fully static and served only over HTTPS, with HTTP Strict
            Transport Security, a strict Content-Security-Policy, and standard
            security headers. There is no database of personal information to be
            breached.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
            I may update this policy from time to time. Any material change will
            be reflected in the “Last updated” date above. Continued use of the
            site after a change means you accept the revised policy.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
            Questions about privacy, or a request about your data? Please reach
            me through the <a class="text-link" href="/contact">contact page</a
            >.
        </p>
    </article>
</Layout>
